snippet.textDisplay: honestly I am not jealous of this lifestyle. I was looking at some alternative, but this thing has so many issues it's a constant work just to get by. u have to get fresh water, yes fresh water to use, then u have limited washing options. electricity is an issue, mobile signal, food, security and safety out there on the ocean, also environmental threats or rather unpredictable weather that can wreck this boat in no time, then there is a constant noise from the sea, limited sleep...etc etc and I can go on. I never lived or sailed, but I read and researched that lifestyle and I admire people who put up with it, because there is really nothing to envy about it even tho it look great, but that's only fraction of the picture

I miss New Hampshire - it's coast, and the Maine coast - Soooo much.

snippet.textDisplay: Newport sure IS America's biggest sailing community - at least the biggest with experienced sailors and racers anyway and the one with the MOST HISTORY as sailing was first POPULARIZED in Newport, RI and it was the first major seaport for the United States in the 1600s and early 1700s before Boston and New York. The majority of  132 years of the America's Cup races were sailed there until 1983 when  Australia ll beat Liberty skippered by Dennis Conner. I lived there for decades and watched the America's Cup defenders sail out of there going back to before the Newport Bridge was built. I remember seeing the crew of the Intrepid and Courageous almost daily walking around Bowen's Wharf after their practices. Some of the old wooden12 Meter boats and 100 foot long wooden J boats are are still there and have been turned into charter boats..

snippet.textDisplay:
Hey Elayna/Riley,
It may sound corny but... to slow his gringing habit, try massaging Lenny's jaw muscles (masseters) from his cheek bones to the lower edge of his jaw. These can be like thick strong rubber bands and Lenny's just discovering them! Try doing it for 3-5 minutes, once or twice a day... in a gentle rythmic roll from top to bottom, front to back. Circular motions. He may let you or he may not, but it's worth a try. Generally toddlers like it or even love it when their parents enjoy helping in a slow, gentle and pleasant way. It may take a few times before you'll notice an improvement, but it's the only thing that may help at this young age. You'll be amazed at those tiny yet firm muscles underneath all those cheeks! Massage out those tiny knots! Good Luck! Dr. Steve

snippet.textDisplay: I’m really sorry about what’s happening in Australia, guys. To me, it’s not something that’s happening in a foreign country but something terrible that’s happening to our home, to our planet. Some say these are the worst fires in the history of our world. If this is not a wake-up call, then I don’t know what it will be … Half the population of the cute Koalas has disappeared and other species are extinct now (the number of total animals affected could be as high as one billion nationwide, according to ecologists from the University of Sydney..) This is all happening in one of the worst droughts in Australia, a heatwave in December broke the record for highest nationwide average temperature, with some places sweltering under temperatures well above 40 degrees Celsius (about 113-120 degrees Fahrenheit). Experts say climate change has worsened the scope and impact of natural disasters like fires and floods -- weather conditions are growing more extreme, and for years, the fires have been starting earlier in the season and spreading with greater intensity. The smoke has got to Argentina … We have the responsibility to speak, everywhere we are, about what each of us can do as individuals to help our planet to heal (you guys have a popular Youtube channel, it can help a lot). We the majorities (humanity) cannot let blind unscrupulous pseudo leaders (politicians) drag our world to destruction. The images of the Australian wildfires are nothing less than apocalyptic (I’m not a religious man but this adjective describes pretty accurately what’s happening in Australia, right now). Australia was the number 1 country on my list of countries I would like to live in if the terrible economic and political situation in my country forces me to leave but now   : I    This tragedy will unfortunately also affect the health of a lot of Australians (and Argentineans; and everybody if it doesn't stop soon) and the economy of Australia... I read ten years ago that Australia would be one of the countries that would be affected the most by global warming but I didn’t think it would be this fast and this crazy… Let us be positive and hope that the majorities will wake-up once and for all and will force the governments of the most powerful countries (all governments) to do what has to be done as soon as possible to stop this craziness. If this is happening now, imagine what it will be like 10 years from now if we don’t do anything …
